<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA7FF95FF5B8DC32F421EC1" blockId="7.[136,635,1748,1775]" box="[136,635,1748,1775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="D0DD81BCFFA7FF95FF5B8DC32F421EC1" bold="true" box="[136,635,1748,1775]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FF5B8DC32F421EC1" bold="true" box="[136,635,1748,1775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FF5B8DC32F371EC1" authority="' Sunny" authorityName="Sunny" box="[136,526,1748,1775]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FF5B8DC32C8B1EC0" bold="true" box="[136,434,1748,1775]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
‘Sunny
</taxonomicName>
Balloon’
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA7FF9AFF5B8C0A2F8318F3" blockId="7.[136,1452,1820,2063]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">
We were unable to determine whether 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FDEB8C0A2E6A1F19" authority="' Sunny" authorityName="Sunny" box="[568,851,1820,1846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FDEB8C0A2FC31F19" box="[568,762,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
‘Sunny
</taxonomicName>
Balloon’ had been previously formally established as a cultivar name, and do so here. Although variously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FC858C5629321F75" authorityName="Von Poellnitz" authorityYear="1934" box="[854,1035,1856,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blossfeldiana">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FC858C5629321F75" box="[854,1035,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. blossfeldiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FBFD8C56298B1F75" box="[1070,1202,1857,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manginii">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FBFD8C56298B1F75" box="[1070,1202,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. manginii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, often as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FAFB8C562C011F51" authority="' Wendy Sunny" authorityName="Wendy Sunny" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manginii">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FAFB8C5628951F75" box="[1320,1452,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. manginii</emphasis>
‘Wendy Sunny
</taxonomicName>
Balloon’” (see for example http://commons.hortipedia.com/wiki/Category: 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FB638C7328131F51" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1200,1322,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Kalanchoe</taxonomicName>
_manginii_ ’Wendy_Sunny_Balloon’), plants available in the horticultural trade under this name, up to now as a trade designation, show a striking resemblance with material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FD408CBA2E611FE9" box="[659,856,1964,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FD408CBA2E611FE9" box="[659,856,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species, with the exception that the flowers are double, not single (
<figureCitation id="13112A55FFA7FF95FE898CC72C991FC5" box="[346,416,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1536,1558]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,533,1511]" captionTargetId="figure-209@7.[151,1435,533,1511]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Close-up of the large, double flowers Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx ‘Sunny Balloon’. Photograph: Gideon F. Smith." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413211/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">Figs 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="13112A55FFA7FF95FE008CC62CDA1FC4" box="[467,483,2001,2027]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1284,1306]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,245,1259]" captionTargetId="figure-47@8.[151,1436,245,1259]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Comparison of the double flowers of Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx ‘Sunny Balloon’ and the regular ones of K. porphyrocalyx var. sambiranensis. Photograph: Gideon F. Smith." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413213/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">7</figureCitation>
). In all other respects material sold under 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FC7C8CC629F11FC5" authority="' Sunny" authorityName="Sunny" box="[943,1224,2000,2026]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FC7C8CC629491FC5" box="[943,1136,2000,2026]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
‘Sunny
</taxonomicName>
Balloon’ is virtually indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FE5F8CE22F761021" box="[396,591,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FE5F8CE22F761021" box="[396,591,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Even though use of 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FCED8CE22E681021" box="[830,849,2037,2062]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K</emphasis>
. ‘Sunny Balloon’ is acceptable, i.e., with reference to the genus name only, it is here proposed that this cultivar, with retention of the cultivar name, is to be associated with the species, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA8FF9AFEFD8BD42F7318F3" authority="' Sunny" authorityName="Sunny" box="[302,586,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFEFD8BD42CC818F3" box="[302,497,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
‘Sunny
</taxonomicName>
Balloon’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF556658FFA8FF9AFF5B8E132F511D11" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413213" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5413213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413213/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" startId="8.[136,229,1284,1306]" targetBox="[151,1436,245,1259]" targetPageId="8">
